HEADWORD: Cowfish
<hw>Cow"fish`</hw> <pr>(kou"f⟦icr⟧sh`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The grampus.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A California dolphin (<spn>Tursiops Gillii</spn>).</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>A marine plectognath fish (<spn>Ostracoin
quadricorne</spn>, and allied species), having two projections, like
horns, in front; -- called also <altname>cuckold</altname>,
<altname>coffer fish</altname>, <altname>trunkfish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

